item.title: [+645] Officials Say Anti-Muslim Images Are 'Protected Speech'
item.description: No charges will be filed against a Minnesota man who placed anti-Muslim posters outside a mosque and other spots. Some of the posters depicted such images as Mohammed engaging in bestiality and an Islamic crescent with a swastika inside it. Benton County Attorney Robert Raupp says religious criticism is protected speech, even if it is offensive.

item.title: [+596] 'Avatar' is the Second Highest Grossing Film of All Time

On Wednesday, "Avatar" passed the $1.12 billion tally by 2003's "The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King" to become the second-highest worldwide gross.

item.title: [+564] Geithner's Told AIG To Withhold $ Info From Public
item.description: An arm of the Federal Reserve, then led by now-Treasury Secretary Timothy Geithner, told bailed-out insurance giant AIG to withhold key details from the public about overpayments that put billions of extra tax dollars in the coffers of major Wall Street firms, most notably Goldman Sachs.
